WEBVTT

00:00.217 --> 00:01.784
(Irisa) Previously on <i> Defiance...</i>

00:01.785 --> 00:03.419
You had him,

00:03.420 --> 00:06.355
Rahm Tak, the leader of
the Votanis Collective.

00:06.356 --> 00:07.790
And if you hadn't have choked,

00:07.791 --> 00:09.926
he'd be a cooling corpse right now

00:09.927 --> 00:12.028
and Defiance would be a whole lot safer.

00:12.029 --> 00:15.765
We're at war, kiddo, and you've
become an unreliable partner.

00:15.766 --> 00:17.867
Rahm Tak is ready to make his move.

00:17.868 --> 00:20.403
I saw him buy a truckload of
weapons from an arms dealer.

00:20.404 --> 00:23.539
The weapons had the Von Bach
Industries logo on them.

00:23.540 --> 00:25.708
When Alak was describing
the arms dealer,

00:25.709 --> 00:27.810
you had a reaction.

00:27.811 --> 00:32.113
Alak is clearly describing my
ex-boyfriend Conrad Von Bach.

00:32.115 --> 00:36.953
My mom and dad, they're
working as spies for the V.C.

00:36.954 --> 00:39.255
[grunting]

00:39.256 --> 00:40.489
Go! Go!

00:40.490 --> 00:42.825
Datak spotted us. He's gonna run.

00:42.826 --> 00:45.895
Grab him now.

00:45.896 --> 00:48.130
[Datak speaking native language]

00:48.131 --> 00:52.602
I think one of us is going to die.

00:52.603 --> 00:55.705
[grunting]

01:00.477 --> 01:04.013
I've been stabbed. I need your help.

01:12.522 --> 01:15.925
I am at a loss for words.

01:17.928 --> 01:21.130
I know how much you and
your wife hate me.

01:21.131 --> 01:23.866
Believe me, the feeling's
more than mutual.

01:27.004 --> 01:28.971
But despite it all,

01:28.972 --> 01:32.875
I really did think you loved our town.

01:34.945 --> 01:38.114
Maybe even as much as I do.

01:38.115 --> 01:41.517
I truly believed that, when
faced with a common enemy,

01:41.518 --> 01:44.053
an enemy that wants to destroy our town

01:44.054 --> 01:47.456
and everything it stands for,

01:47.457 --> 01:49.859
that you would stand with us.

01:49.860 --> 01:54.864
I would never say you are a good man,

01:54.865 --> 01:58.534
but siding with a mass murderer?

01:58.535 --> 02:01.537
I thought you were better than that.

02:01.538 --> 02:06.342
It is with a heavy heart
that I vote to convict.

02:06.343 --> 02:08.276
[marble clinks in cup]

02:13.984 --> 02:15.284
[clink]

02:19.089 --> 02:20.689
[clink]

02:21.591 --> 02:23.592
[clink]

02:24.494 --> 02:26.295
[clink]

02:27.230 --> 02:29.031
[clink]

02:29.933 --> 02:32.001
[clink]

02:34.338 --> 02:36.172
[whistles]

02:36.173 --> 02:38.007
[clink]

02:40.000 --> 02:46.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:51.021 --> 02:55.858
Datak Tarr, this panel has found
you guilty of high treason,

02:55.859 --> 02:58.894
which carries a sentence
of death by hanging.

02:58.895 --> 03:03.199
If you wish, you may now
make a brief statement.

03:03.200 --> 03:07.136
Did my wife do that to your face?

03:07.137 --> 03:08.938
It's a good look for you.

03:08.939 --> 03:10.306
[scoffs]

03:10.307 --> 03:14.076
[rock music]

03:14.077 --> 03:22.184
♪ ♪

03:39.636 --> 03:42.004
Nice town, Benedict.

03:42.005 --> 03:44.073
Think I should buy it?

03:44.074 --> 03:47.643
I think you should buy an airplane.

03:47.644 --> 03:49.178
You're a hopeless romantic.

03:49.179 --> 03:51.347
Watch the truck.

03:51.348 --> 03:52.728
Okay.

03:59.189 --> 04:01.223
Thanks, Augusta.

04:03.193 --> 04:05.928
No, these aren't really
me either, are they?

04:05.929 --> 04:09.732
Um, how about the blue frames?

04:16.540 --> 04:17.973
What's with the sign?

04:17.974 --> 04:19.875
My husband and I are moving west.

04:19.875 --> 04:21.877
It's not safe in Defiance.

04:21.878 --> 04:23.045
Not safe?

04:23.046 --> 04:25.514
They say soldiers are
coming to kill humans.

04:25.515 --> 04:28.150
Most of my friends have
left town already.

04:28.151 --> 04:29.718
Well, you're smart to get out.

04:29.719 --> 04:32.955
I'm heading west myself after
I conclude a bit of business.

04:32.956 --> 04:35.991
If you're ever in AngelArc, look me up.

04:35.992 --> 04:37.860
- You're a Von Bach?
- Yeah.

04:37.861 --> 04:39.395
Really?

04:39.396 --> 04:41.697
It's been a long time, Conrad.

04:41.698 --> 04:43.632
Jess.

04:43.633 --> 04:45.034
Been a while.

04:45.035 --> 04:46.635
You look good.

04:46.636 --> 04:49.237
I have two questions for you.

04:49.238 --> 04:52.874
One, did you sell weapons
to the Votanis Collective?

04:55.411 --> 04:57.111
Guilty as charged.

04:57.112 --> 04:59.614
But you understand, this is...

04:59.615 --> 05:01.349
Oh.

05:04.954 --> 05:06.554
You had another question?

05:06.555 --> 05:09.858
Did you bring weapons for us?

05:09.859 --> 05:12.193
You never were much into foreplay.

05:14.196 --> 05:17.265
[dramatic music]

05:19.095 --> 05:23.338
Subtitle sync and corrections
by awaqeded for www.addic7ed.com.

05:25.641 --> 05:30.044
Snapdragon bolt-rifles,
cold-fire hand cannons...

05:32.114 --> 05:33.281
Particle Overmag.

05:33.282 --> 05:34.883
Beautiful weapon.

05:34.884 --> 05:36.818
I'll say.

05:36.819 --> 05:38.119
See?

05:38.120 --> 05:40.722
It's what Von Bach
Industries are all about.

05:40.723 --> 05:44.092
Providing quality weapons for
people to defend themselves.

05:44.093 --> 05:45.426
And here I thought you were a family

05:45.427 --> 05:47.762
of ruthless war profiteers
who cared about nothing

05:47.763 --> 05:49.464
but the bottom line.

05:49.465 --> 05:53.234
The Butcher of Yosemite
is calling me ruthless?

05:53.235 --> 05:54.235
Ouch.

05:54.236 --> 05:55.670
You supplied arms to the V.C.

05:55.671 --> 05:57.171
Aw, come on. We're businessmen.

05:57.172 --> 05:59.007
We don't discriminate.
We don't take sides.

05:59.008 --> 06:01.109
We sell weapons to those
who can afford them.

06:01.110 --> 06:02.210
Nolan.

06:02.211 --> 06:03.444
You've put a lot of innocent lives at risk.

06:03.445 --> 06:05.847
You choose your next words carefully.

06:05.848 --> 06:07.115
Aloe Vera.

06:07.116 --> 06:08.449
[weapon whirs]

06:08.450 --> 06:10.285
Voice-matching activation.

06:10.286 --> 06:13.454
I say when my guns work.
I say when they don't.

06:13.455 --> 06:14.822
Don't worry, we'll match it to your voice

06:14.823 --> 06:16.291
once we've settled on a price.

06:16.292 --> 06:18.126
Stop showing off. What's the number?

06:18.127 --> 06:20.662
Still no foreplay.

06:20.663 --> 06:23.431
I'm telling you, Jess,
you're missing out.

06:31.373 --> 06:34.175
All right, It's a zero. is.

06:34.176 --> 06:35.443
Consider the weapons a gift.

06:35.444 --> 06:36.711
A gift.

06:36.712 --> 06:37.979
Are you joking?

06:37.980 --> 06:40.048
Von Bachs never joke
when it comes to business.

06:40.049 --> 06:41.279
That's what makes us so boring.

06:41.280 --> 06:42.450
What's the catch?

06:42.451 --> 06:43.651
The catch is, you buy me a drink.

06:43.652 --> 06:46.654
How's that sound?

06:46.655 --> 06:47.989
Do it.

06:47.990 --> 06:50.091
Drinks are on the house.

06:53.896 --> 06:58.633
Anything for the team.

06:58.634 --> 06:59.834
Goldenrod.

06:59.835 --> 07:01.969
[weapon whirs]

07:03.872 --> 07:06.174
They've got about as far as
they can with the shovels.

07:06.175 --> 07:08.343
We're about to bring in the drill.

07:08.344 --> 07:10.845
Good.

07:10.846 --> 07:14.015
I suppose there's no point in
putting this off any longer.

07:19.355 --> 07:21.289
[grunts]

07:27.396 --> 07:29.697
This is going to hurt, Bebe.

07:29.698 --> 07:33.034
Purity requires sacrifice.

07:36.572 --> 07:39.674
[groaning]

08:00.761 --> 08:04.731
Hey, kiddo.

08:04.732 --> 08:07.233
Nice job on those flyers.

08:07.234 --> 08:09.402
Don't make fun of me.

08:09.403 --> 08:10.770
What?

08:10.771 --> 08:12.739
"Nice work on those flyers"?

08:12.740 --> 08:14.731
Don't you think I want to pick
up a gun and defend the town

08:14.732 --> 08:15.475
like everybody else?

08:15.476 --> 08:16.509
I wasn't making fun.

08:16.510 --> 08:18.078
Right.

08:18.079 --> 08:19.646
So I'm just hypersensitive.
Is that what you're saying?

08:19.647 --> 08:21.848
No! No.

08:21.849 --> 08:23.750
Whatever.

08:23.751 --> 08:26.586
I'll make copies.

08:30.925 --> 08:33.726
Almost done.

08:36.429 --> 08:40.200
You were in town today.

08:40.201 --> 08:43.203
Any news of my husband?

08:43.203 --> 08:46.873
He's been sentenced to die.

08:46.874 --> 08:48.274
When?

08:48.275 --> 08:49.676
In three days.

08:49.677 --> 08:51.211
[sighs]

08:51.212 --> 08:55.315
I'm sure you'd like some time
alone with your thoughts.

08:55.316 --> 08:58.685
You can rest in my quarters
while I'm in the mines.

08:58.686 --> 09:01.221
I've caused so much trouble,

09:01.222 --> 09:04.891
yet you show me nothing but kindness.

09:06.727 --> 09:09.896
Wake me when you return.

09:09.897 --> 09:12.198
_

09:12.806 --> 09:13.940
_

09:14.341 --> 09:17.105
