09:17.905 --> 09:21.231
_

09:21.642 --> 09:23.584
_

09:23.789 --> 09:25.691
_

09:26.808 --> 09:28.515
_

09:30.206 --> 09:31.249
_

09:31.613 --> 09:32.520
_

09:34.221 --> 09:37.023
Forgive my daughter.

09:37.024 --> 09:40.760
She's prone to tantrums.

09:40.761 --> 09:44.130
There is nothing to forgive.

09:52.689 --> 09:55.395
_

09:56.521 --> 09:58.770
_

09:59.680 --> 10:01.347
Speak English.

10:01.348 --> 10:04.350
You need the practice.

10:06.754 --> 10:08.121
This town will turn on us

10:08.122 --> 10:10.790
if they learn you're protecting a spy.

10:10.791 --> 10:14.360
I have no intent in telling them.

10:14.361 --> 10:16.996
Do you?

10:20.034 --> 10:21.701
(Berlin) So how's your nose?

10:21.702 --> 10:25.104
It hurts.

10:25.105 --> 10:27.140
Thank you for the guns.

10:27.141 --> 10:31.044
You're welcome for the guns.

10:31.045 --> 10:32.879
How much trouble are you in?

10:32.880 --> 10:35.615
Oh, well, very soon expect
to make the transition

10:35.616 --> 10:38.651
from black sheep of the family

10:38.652 --> 10:42.388
to disinherited dead black
sheep of the family.

10:42.389 --> 10:45.425
So why did you do it?

10:45.426 --> 10:48.661
Well, it was the only
gesture I could think of

10:48.662 --> 10:50.930
big enough to impress you.

10:54.602 --> 10:55.702
No, no, no.

10:55.703 --> 10:58.671
Connie, you and me are ancient history.

10:58.672 --> 11:01.241
- You and I.
- Don't correct my grammar.

11:01.242 --> 11:02.242
You know I hate that.

11:02.243 --> 11:04.310
Yeah, I know.

11:04.311 --> 11:05.845
I know.

11:05.846 --> 11:08.681
So did I?

11:10.317 --> 11:12.518
- Did you what?
- Impress you.

11:15.456 --> 11:16.756
I've missed you.

11:16.757 --> 11:20.126
You say that, but I'm not sure you do.

11:20.127 --> 11:21.995
I came home from the tour,

11:21.996 --> 11:24.597
and our Redwood apartment was empty.

11:24.598 --> 11:27.433
Furniture gone. You took the dog.

11:27.434 --> 11:29.269
And your mother's lawyer was there

11:29.270 --> 11:31.771
with a briefcase full of scri.

11:31.772 --> 11:33.706
Told me that you had
reconsidered the wisdom

11:33.707 --> 11:35.642
of our relationship.

11:35.643 --> 11:37.343
What. I never said that.

11:37.344 --> 11:38.478
Come on.

11:38.479 --> 11:39.712
I never said that.

11:39.713 --> 11:41.527
I was under the impression
that you dumped me.

11:41.528 --> 11:42.715
What?

11:42.716 --> 11:43.850
Yeah.

11:43.851 --> 11:45.618
Mother told me she offered you cash

11:45.619 --> 11:47.820
to break off the engagement

11:47.821 --> 11:49.555
and you accepted.

11:49.556 --> 11:51.610
She said that proved you were
only after our family money.

11:51.611 --> 11:52.759
No, no, no, no, no.

11:52.760 --> 11:56.162
What really happened was,
I shot a hole in the briefcase,

11:56.163 --> 11:58.431
and then I shot your
mother's lawyer in the foot.

11:58.432 --> 12:00.099
- Is that the truth?
- Yeah.

12:00.100 --> 12:02.735
It felt great.

12:02.736 --> 12:05.872
Well, looks like Mother
outsmarted us both.

12:05.873 --> 12:08.574
No one ever called her stupid.

12:08.575 --> 12:12.512
I'm so sorry. I...

12:12.513 --> 12:15.882
I just wish... I wish you'd come...
told me the truth.

12:15.883 --> 12:20.687
Pretty sure you have that backwards.

12:20.688 --> 12:22.789
[sighs]

12:26.193 --> 12:28.795
So you're happy here in Defiance?

12:31.932 --> 12:35.034
When the E-Rep was here, I felt safe.

12:35.035 --> 12:36.736
There was this guy Tommy,

12:36.737 --> 12:40.373
and he was gentle and kind

12:40.374 --> 12:43.810
and had a great ass.

12:43.811 --> 12:46.913
Okay, so now I'm jealous.

12:48.382 --> 12:51.042
Don't be. He's dead.

13:02.796 --> 13:04.797
You want to go upstairs?

13:04.798 --> 13:07.200
Yeah, I do.

13:14.975 --> 13:18.077
[grunting]

13:20.547 --> 13:21.714
[grunts]

13:24.318 --> 13:26.285
- You're late.
- Long night.

13:26.286 --> 13:28.221
I bet.

13:28.222 --> 13:29.989
Well, decent turn-out.

13:29.990 --> 13:33.092
It'll do, for a start.

13:33.093 --> 13:35.161
Okay, recruits!

13:35.162 --> 13:36.996
Fall in.

13:48.275 --> 13:50.309
[sighs] Here you go.

13:50.310 --> 13:51.744
No, thanks. I brought my own.

13:51.745 --> 13:55.148
Come on, that's an antique.

13:55.149 --> 13:56.949
Weather vane.

13:56.950 --> 13:58.851
[gunshots]

14:03.190 --> 14:05.058
She gets the job done.

14:05.059 --> 14:06.626
I guess so.

14:06.627 --> 14:07.860
What's your name?

14:07.861 --> 14:10.997
Ranikar, but you can call me Zera.

14:10.998 --> 14:14.000
All right, Zero, you can shoot.
Who taught you?

14:14.001 --> 14:15.501
My dad.

14:15.502 --> 14:18.704
I built him that gun myself
from scrap parts and old metal.

14:18.705 --> 14:20.940
Took me three months
to get the scope right.

14:20.941 --> 14:22.208
I'm Indur, by the way.

14:22.209 --> 14:24.043
Good to have you here.

14:24.044 --> 14:26.546
Thank you. So this is it?

14:26.547 --> 14:27.780
This is all you got?

14:27.781 --> 14:29.882
We're in the process of building.

14:41.361 --> 14:43.462
Bebe!

14:46.533 --> 14:47.971
_

14:52.025 --> 14:53.080
_

14:54.112 --> 14:57.115
_

15:00.222 --> 15:03.243
_

15:12.280 --> 15:13.647
That's it, come on.

15:13.702 --> 15:15.002
- Pick those legs up.
- Four!

15:15.003 --> 15:18.506
- Let's go. That's better.
- Five!

15:18.507 --> 15:20.808
- All right, good.
- Six!

15:20.809 --> 15:23.144
- Seven!
- Let's go, people.

15:23.145 --> 15:24.879
- Eight!
- What are you doing?

15:24.880 --> 15:26.280
- Where's your daughter?
- Nine!

15:26.281 --> 15:27.815
- What?
- I asked you a question.

15:27.816 --> 15:30.117
- Where's your daughter?
- Ten!

15:30.118 --> 15:32.420
I don't have time for your questions.

15:32.421 --> 15:34.288
I'm trying to get people
ready for battle.

15:34.289 --> 15:35.523
Don't waste my time!

15:35.524 --> 15:37.058
I am going to keep wasting your time

15:37.059 --> 15:38.793
until you give me a straight answer.

15:38.794 --> 15:40.717
_

15:40.862 --> 15:42.148
Most of these kids have read

15:42.149 --> 15:44.255
<i>The Amazing Goddess of the Badlands.</i>

15:44.256 --> 15:45.051
_

15:45.379 --> 15:46.742
_

15:48.790 --> 15:50.660
And I want to know where she is.

15:51.316 --> 15:54.118
Why isn't the Amazing Goddess
fighting by their side?

15:56.354 --> 15:59.823
My daughter's been
through a lot recently.

15:59.824 --> 16:03.961
Right now she's not capable
of picking up a weapon.

16:03.962 --> 16:06.530
But my child is?

16:06.531 --> 16:08.565
And you should know
we're not the only recruits

16:08.566 --> 16:10.000
asking these questions.

16:10.001 --> 16:13.203
Many among us think the
Votanis Collective

16:13.204 --> 16:14.505
is a human problem.

16:14.506 --> 16:17.841
Really? Really, a human problem?

16:17.842 --> 16:19.443
And they believe that Rahm Tak

16:19.444 --> 16:23.013
would treat the Votans with
kindness if he took Defiance.

16:23.014 --> 16:24.014
That's a fantasy.

16:24.015 --> 16:25.482
That's what some believe.

16:25.483 --> 16:26.984
Do you believe that?

16:28.353 --> 16:29.987
Do you believe that?

16:29.988 --> 16:32.790
I believe that if your family isn't going

16:32.791 --> 16:36.160
to fight for Defiance,
then neither is mine.

16:40.165 --> 16:43.634
Sorry. He's my dad.

16:46.204 --> 16:48.038
Anyone else?

16:57.182 --> 16:59.917
Keep them moving. Let's go.

16:59.918 --> 17:02.386
Okay, and...

17:02.387 --> 17:07.691
16, 17, 18!

17:12.430 --> 17:14.397
Thank you for coming.

17:24.563 --> 17:26.897
What happened to you?

17:26.898 --> 17:29.868
Spent the day in basic training.

17:29.869 --> 17:32.937
Nolan's whipping us into shape
to face your good pal Rahm Tak.

17:32.938 --> 17:36.741
Rahm's no friend of mine.

17:36.742 --> 17:37.909
Any word of your mother?

17:37.910 --> 17:41.046
They haven't caught her yet.

17:41.047 --> 17:44.983
They never will. She's too smart.

17:44.984 --> 17:47.118
Where's my grandson?

17:47.119 --> 17:48.620
Home.

17:48.621 --> 17:50.221
Ignoring a condemned man's wishes,

17:50.222 --> 17:53.591
it's kind of petty, don't you think?

17:53.592 --> 17:55.293
You helped Rahm Tak,

17:55.294 --> 17:57.629
and now that psychopath
is coming for us,

17:57.630 --> 17:59.564
and if we can't fight him off,

17:59.565 --> 18:02.567
well, then my half-human child

18:02.568 --> 18:04.002
is going to be brutally murdered.

18:04.003 --> 18:07.505
So, no, Dad, Luke will not
be visiting you ever.

18:07.506 --> 18:09.274
I had no choice.

18:09.275 --> 18:10.642
There's always a choice.

18:10.643 --> 18:12.577
Look, the minute you got home,

18:12.578 --> 18:14.245
you and Mom should have
warned Nolan and Amanda.

18:14.246 --> 18:16.214
You were Rahm's hostage.
He would have killed you.

18:16.215 --> 18:17.382
I escaped.

18:17.383 --> 18:20.285
Well, how was I supposed
to know that would happen?

18:20.286 --> 18:22.954
You know, even if Rahm Tak
had killed me, so what?

18:22.955 --> 18:26.191
I would have died protecting
my child and my home.

18:26.192 --> 18:28.293
I'd be with Christie now.

18:28.294 --> 18:31.129
My death would have meaning.

18:31.130 --> 18:35.099
You... you should have told the truth.

18:36.168 --> 18:38.303
You and Mom should have helped.

18:38.304 --> 18:40.972
Don't leave. Please, wait.

18:40.973 --> 18:45.043
I've failed you, Alak.
I've failed our family.

18:45.044 --> 18:48.046
If I could change my actions,
if I could murder Rahm Tak

18:48.047 --> 18:50.782
and raise the Arch, I would do so.

18:50.783 --> 18:52.717
If killing myself and your mother

18:52.718 --> 18:56.688
would bring back Christie,
I would cut both our throats.

18:56.689 --> 18:59.057
But my time is done here.

18:59.058 --> 19:01.960
I'm out of choices.

19:01.961 --> 19:05.497
So I must ask

19:05.498 --> 19:07.665
_

19:08.801 --> 19:10.902
You know, it's not really the best time.

19:10.903 --> 19:14.372
Please, hear me out.

19:14.373 --> 19:16.875
I want you to go to Amanda.

19:16.876 --> 19:20.612
Tell her that I cannot
face human justice.

19:20.613 --> 19:23.915
I want to die properly.

19:23.916 --> 19:26.576
At the hands of our own people.

19:28.988 --> 19:31.456
On a shaming rack.

19:35.427 --> 19:38.196
Just so that I'm clear,

19:38.197 --> 19:40.398
rather than a quick death by hanging,

19:40.399 --> 19:45.403
you're asking to be tortured
to death by weights

19:45.404 --> 19:48.039
slowly pulling your arms
and legs from their sockets.

19:48.040 --> 19:51.509
This is what you're asking?

19:51.510 --> 19:55.580
It's the only way to remove the
stain from my immortal soul.

19:58.617 --> 20:00.752
Alak.

20:00.753 --> 20:02.854
I'll see what I can do.

20:04.023 --> 20:07.592
[door opens and closes]

20:07.593 --> 20:09.294
No, no way, Nolan. I won't do it.

20:09.295 --> 20:10.895
You think I want to be
asking you to do this?

20:10.896 --> 20:12.197
I know you don't want to fight.

20:12.198 --> 20:15.033
Then stop trying to make me.

20:15.034 --> 20:17.268
You don't join the militia,
I can't defend the town.

20:17.269 --> 20:19.091
They're going to comin here,
they're going to drag

20:19.092 --> 20:21.105
every human being they can
find into Darby Square,

20:21.106 --> 20:23.708
line them up, and shoot them
in the head ten at a time.

20:23.709 --> 20:26.077
This is how we stop them.

20:26.078 --> 20:28.479
Why? Huh?

20:28.480 --> 20:31.449
Why does everyone hurt each other?

20:31.450 --> 20:34.085
Why is our world like this?

20:34.086 --> 20:36.087
I don't know, kid.

20:36.088 --> 20:38.790
This is how it is.

20:38.791 --> 20:40.558
You ever get scared?

20:42.161 --> 20:44.629
All the time.

20:46.265 --> 20:47.832
Are you scared now?

20:49.602 --> 20:52.136
Yeah.

20:52.137 --> 20:54.005
And tired.

20:54.006 --> 20:55.106
[chuckles]

21:01.547 --> 21:03.414
I love you.

21:12.858 --> 21:15.293
- [snarls]
- [gasps]

21:17.396 --> 21:20.998
You're dirty. You need to be cleaned.

21:22.334 --> 21:24.869
Actually, I bathed fairly recent...

21:24.870 --> 21:26.650
- I insist.
- [screams]

21:29.975 --> 21:32.610
You're very pretty.

21:32.611 --> 21:34.646
Soft.

21:34.647 --> 21:37.148
[sniffs]

21:37.149 --> 21:41.219
You smell nice. I see why
my father enjoys you.

21:42.354 --> 21:44.689
You flatter me.

21:44.690 --> 21:48.960
Omec beauty is the standard by
which the rest of us are judged.

21:48.961 --> 21:53.231
For my people, a Castithan
slave was a mark of status.

21:53.232 --> 21:55.700
The finest sparked bitter competitions

21:55.701 --> 21:59.370
to see who could spoil
them with expensive gifts

21:59.371 --> 22:01.873
and fine perfumes.

22:01.874 --> 22:04.676
But when the enchanted
Castithan was used up,

22:04.677 --> 22:07.578
they'd be put down in the pens...

22:07.579 --> 22:10.348
force-fed, oiled

22:10.349 --> 22:13.651
until it was fit to be consumed.

22:13.652 --> 22:18.323
You know, my father tires of his
concubines faster than most.

22:18.324 --> 22:20.992
I've been told that when
he's done with one,

22:20.993 --> 22:25.163
he'd give it to his
children as a living toy.

22:25.164 --> 22:28.933
It is a great honor to
devour your father's whore.

22:31.904 --> 22:36.040
You know, I think I'm clean now.

22:36.041 --> 22:39.143
[breathing heavily]

22:41.280 --> 22:43.940
You're more trouble than you're worth.

22:45.551 --> 22:47.585
[panting]

22:47.586 --> 22:49.253
[gasps]

22:51.590 --> 22:55.293
Please. I will leave here.

23:00.366 --> 23:03.026
Just tell me what you want.

23:05.270 --> 23:06.404
[snarls]

23:06.405 --> 23:07.939
[gasps]

23:07.940 --> 23:10.608
I want you

23:10.609 --> 23:12.543
to die

23:12.544 --> 23:15.113
frightened.

23:15.114 --> 23:16.848
[whimpers]

23:18.851 --> 23:20.351
[both growling]

23:20.352 --> 23:23.388
[chokes]

23:23.389 --> 23:27.358
I carefully consider the
commands I give you, Kindzi.

23:27.359 --> 23:31.162
I expect you to obey them precisely.

23:31.163 --> 23:32.663
Now in a moment, I'm going to relieve

23:32.664 --> 23:35.266
the pressure from your throat,

23:35.267 --> 23:38.769
and you will apologize to Stahma.

23:40.305 --> 23:41.906
[gasping]

23:45.144 --> 23:48.079
I apologize...

23:48.080 --> 23:50.248
Stahma.

23:52.651 --> 23:55.052
Think nothing of it.

24:01.444 --> 24:04.012
[TV chatter]

24:04.013 --> 24:07.182
Conrad?

24:07.183 --> 24:09.718
[film reel clicking]

24:11.354 --> 24:14.356
What you've done to it.

24:14.357 --> 24:16.692
<i>All That Heaven Allows.</i>

24:16.693 --> 24:20.629
I remembered how much
you loved Douglas Sirk.

24:20.630 --> 24:23.165
I don't know what to say.

24:23.166 --> 24:25.867
Well, how about saying,

24:25.868 --> 24:28.303
"Wow, Conrad, that was
incredibly thoughtful,

24:28.304 --> 24:32.507
and I wish our time
together would never end"?

24:32.508 --> 24:34.876
All good things must.

24:36.713 --> 24:38.680
They don't have to.

24:38.681 --> 24:41.650
Not this time.

24:41.651 --> 24:44.152
Jess, I'm leaving tomorrow.

24:44.153 --> 24:46.154
It's a big truck.

24:46.155 --> 24:50.892
Plenty of room for an extra passenger.

24:50.893 --> 24:54.362
What, are you just going to
take me away from all of this?

24:55.932 --> 24:57.666
You know, when I agreed to come here,

24:57.667 --> 25:00.335
I didn't know what to expect.

25:00.336 --> 25:02.404
Packed up the film,

25:02.405 --> 25:04.339
the guns,

25:04.340 --> 25:06.708
hoped for the best.

25:06.709 --> 25:08.210
And?

25:08.211 --> 25:11.379
The best was here.

25:14.083 --> 25:16.184
I can't go away with you.

25:16.185 --> 25:17.185
[sighs]

25:17.186 --> 25:18.253
Defiance is my home,

25:18.254 --> 25:20.789
and I need to be here to defend it.

25:20.790 --> 25:25.227
Defiance isn't your home.

25:25.228 --> 25:28.497
You were deployed here
by the Earth Republic.

25:29.399 --> 25:30.866
Well, guess what.

25:30.867 --> 25:34.035
E-Rep is dead.

25:34.036 --> 25:37.939
Your boyfriend Tommy is dead.

25:37.940 --> 25:40.275
I'm alive,

25:40.276 --> 25:42.978
and I'm here.

25:42.979 --> 25:46.181
And I want a future with the
girl I never stopped loving.

25:51.521 --> 25:53.121
Let's just watch the movie.

25:53.122 --> 25:55.991
(Cary on TV) I just hadn't
thought about marriage.

25:55.992 --> 25:58.226
(Ron on TV) Why do you think
I've been seeing you?

26:05.268 --> 26:09.271
Alak tells me you've asked
to die on the shaming rack.

26:10.573 --> 26:13.375
What's your angle?

26:13.376 --> 26:15.677
I have quite possibly
delivered this town

26:15.678 --> 26:18.580
into the hands of a madman.

26:18.581 --> 26:20.182
I've destroyed my family.

26:20.183 --> 26:23.919
I've put the lives of
everyone I love at risk.

26:23.920 --> 26:26.688
For a Castithan, atonement
can only be achieved

26:26.689 --> 26:28.990
by what you humans would call

26:28.991 --> 26:31.860
"rough justice."

26:31.861 --> 26:36.364
I could explain this in greater
detail, but what's the point?

26:36.365 --> 26:39.100
My reasons don't matter.

26:39.101 --> 26:41.503
I suggest you ask yourself
if you'd prefer my death

26:41.504 --> 26:46.074
be quick and clean

26:46.075 --> 26:50.312
or a slow, agonizing public spectacle?

26:50.313 --> 26:52.314
Hmm.

26:56.419 --> 26:58.520
Your request is granted.

27:06.062 --> 27:07.128
Hey.

27:07.129 --> 27:09.297
What's up?

27:09.298 --> 27:11.333
I wanted to talk to you.

27:11.334 --> 27:13.034
By all means.

27:13.035 --> 27:14.736
I want details.

27:14.737 --> 27:16.805
What's going on with Von Bach, huh?

27:16.806 --> 27:18.874
You've been seeing a lot of him.

27:18.875 --> 27:22.043
I know. Crazy, right?

27:22.044 --> 27:26.081
All these years hating the guy,
I forgot how much I liked him.

27:26.082 --> 27:29.050
Well, I really like his guns.

27:29.051 --> 27:32.387
So I guess everyone's happy.

27:32.388 --> 27:34.422
[sighs]

27:41.664 --> 27:43.498
What's wrong?

27:43.499 --> 27:45.734
Conrad asked me to go away with him.

27:45.735 --> 27:47.369
What do you mean?

27:47.370 --> 27:49.070
Leave Defiance?

27:49.071 --> 27:50.872
For good?

27:50.873 --> 27:52.507
[sighs]

27:52.508 --> 27:55.610
Conrad Von Bach broke your heart.

27:55.611 --> 27:59.047
Actually, it was his family
that was more of the issue.

27:59.048 --> 28:01.283
All right, now you're
just making excuses.

28:01.284 --> 28:03.351
I mean, come on, Jess, you can't
seriously be considering this.

28:03.352 --> 28:04.753
He loves me.

28:04.754 --> 28:07.289
Oh, please.

28:07.290 --> 28:10.859
What... and do you love him?

28:10.860 --> 28:13.395
I don't know. Maybe.

28:13.396 --> 28:17.098
Okay, well, if he truly loves
you, he'll wait for you.

28:17.099 --> 28:19.034
We're in the middle of a
crisis at the moment.

28:19.035 --> 28:20.035
We're leaving tomorrow.

28:20.036 --> 28:21.703
Plans change.

28:21.704 --> 28:23.371
- Talk to him.
- Amanda.

28:23.372 --> 28:24.806
- I'll go with you.
- Please.

28:24.807 --> 28:25.874
We'll figure this out together.

28:25.875 --> 28:28.209
I don't want to figure it out.

28:28.210 --> 28:30.578
Then what do you want?

28:32.181 --> 28:34.182
Your support.

28:35.952 --> 28:38.453
[sighs]

28:38.454 --> 28:40.822
What's the big rush?

28:42.558 --> 28:44.559
I'm scared.

28:44.560 --> 28:46.161
Join the club.

28:46.162 --> 28:48.496
You know what my childhood was like.

28:48.497 --> 28:51.481
After the raiders killed my
family, I was alone, and then...

28:51.482 --> 28:52.224
Are we trading childhood

28:52.225 --> 28:53.843
- sob stories here?
- When they would turn their backs around,

28:53.844 --> 28:55.168
- I would just steal their food.
- Because if that's what we're doing,

28:55.169 --> 28:57.849
- I will win.
- Will you stop? Will you just listen to me?

29:00.147 --> 29:03.483
I was afraid all the time.

29:03.484 --> 29:06.119
I was scared of getting caught.

29:06.120 --> 29:09.823
I was scared of dying.
I was scared of not dying.

29:09.824 --> 29:12.325
And then when I was 16,
I joined the Earth Republic,

29:12.326 --> 29:16.396
and then suddenly, there
was food and clothes

29:16.397 --> 29:20.467
and people who kept track of
me, and they were my family.

29:20.468 --> 29:22.736
Then it was all taken away,

29:22.737 --> 29:27.407
and now I am just that scared,
lonely kid all over again.

29:27.408 --> 29:29.909
Look, you still have family, all right?

29:29.910 --> 29:33.480
I'm your family, and you
cannot turn your back on me.

29:33.481 --> 29:36.816
Not now, not when I'm trying
to hold all of this together.

29:36.817 --> 29:40.854
For me, family has to be
more than good intentions.

29:40.855 --> 29:45.258
And I don't think that you can
protect us from what's coming.

29:45.259 --> 29:49.029
Not me, not yourself, and not this town.

29:49.030 --> 29:51.231
I'm so sorry.

29:51.232 --> 29:53.199
[scoffs]

29:57.965 --> 30:00.858
You're a coward.

30:33.028 --> 30:34.195
[door creaks open]

30:39.534 --> 30:40.901
I'm not sure if Amanda told you...

30:40.902 --> 30:42.536
She told me.

30:42.537 --> 30:45.206
Defiance thanks you for your service.

30:47.242 --> 30:49.043
It wasn't an easy choice, Nolan.

30:49.044 --> 30:50.611
You know how much
Defiance means to me,

30:50.612 --> 30:52.347
and if I had any other option...

30:52.348 --> 30:53.304
Like I said,

30:53.305 --> 30:56.817
Defiance thanks you for your service.

31:12.300 --> 31:14.690
Reporting for duty.

31:17.139 --> 31:19.740
Good to have you on board, soldier.

31:25.447 --> 31:27.766
Hey, look, the Amazing Goddess.

31:35.690 --> 31:38.492
Thank you.

31:38.493 --> 31:40.761
Okay.

31:40.762 --> 31:42.096
Here you go, boys.

31:42.097 --> 31:44.598
[gunfire]

31:52.007 --> 31:53.607
You're a machine.

31:53.608 --> 31:56.911
You should see me when
I'm hunting kanga-rats.

31:56.912 --> 31:58.946
So what do you think?

31:58.947 --> 32:01.482
For the most part,
it's what we expected...

32:01.483 --> 32:03.350
pow farmers and shopkeepers,

32:03.351 --> 32:07.087
inexperienced but doing their best.

32:07.088 --> 32:10.758
There is some real talent
here, Indur's kid.

32:10.759 --> 32:12.660
He may be inexperienced,
but he's probably

32:12.661 --> 32:16.130
the best long-range
shooter I've ever seen.

32:16.131 --> 32:17.731
We've got a handful
of professional soldiers

32:17.732 --> 32:20.534
like myself.

32:20.535 --> 32:22.976
Throw in Irisa, we might
just have the beginnings

32:22.977 --> 32:24.944
of a strike force.

32:26.680 --> 32:28.247
[exhales]

32:33.887 --> 32:36.889
[dramatic music]

32:36.890 --> 32:38.157
♪ ♪

32:38.158 --> 32:41.260
[breathing heavily]

32:42.195 --> 32:43.295
[grunts]

32:45.432 --> 32:51.070
♪ ♪

32:51.071 --> 32:54.240
[gasping]

32:54.241 --> 32:56.976
Irisa.

32:58.712 --> 33:02.048
Tommy, it's me.

33:02.049 --> 33:04.550
Tommy, I'm so sorry.

33:04.551 --> 33:07.219
[sobs]

33:07.220 --> 33:09.622
I'm so sorry, Tommy.

33:09.623 --> 33:12.858
I'm so sorry.

33:12.859 --> 33:14.462
I wish I could take it all back.

33:14.463 --> 33:16.295
- Okay, okay. Come on.
- I wish...

33:16.296 --> 33:18.064
I wish I could take it back.

33:18.065 --> 33:20.232
Come on. Get her out of here.

33:20.233 --> 33:23.202
Just don't let this fall apart.

33:28.575 --> 33:30.835
All right, people. Come
on, let's bring it in.

33:33.313 --> 33:35.881
Sorry.

33:35.882 --> 33:39.118
I'm sorry.

33:39.119 --> 33:41.120
(Nolan) I screwed up.

33:41.121 --> 33:42.788
I dragged my daughter down here

33:42.789 --> 33:46.625
when I knew she was
in no condition to fight,

33:46.626 --> 33:48.928
because Indur made a good point.

33:48.929 --> 33:50.896
A fair point.

33:50.897 --> 33:53.065
How can we ask of you
that you risk your own lives

33:53.066 --> 33:56.135
and the lives of your
children defending Defiance

33:56.136 --> 33:58.904
unless we're prepared to do the same?

33:58.905 --> 34:00.339
Fair point.

34:00.340 --> 34:02.808
But here's the thing, people.

34:02.809 --> 34:04.610
Throughout history,

34:04.611 --> 34:09.415
the strong have been called
upon to defend the weak.

34:09.416 --> 34:12.485
I know it's not fair.

34:12.485 --> 34:17.123
But those of you who
serve, sweat, and bleed

34:17.123 --> 34:18.924
and push your bodies
past their breaking point

34:18.925 --> 34:22.628
spend endless hours in combat training

34:22.629 --> 34:27.032
for those who cannot show up themselves,

34:27.033 --> 34:29.135
who are incapable, or
who can't be bothered

34:29.136 --> 34:33.539
or just won't do it.

34:33.540 --> 34:37.342
The strong defend the weak.

34:37.344 --> 34:39.879
It's not fair,

34:39.880 --> 34:42.380
but it is right.

34:42.382 --> 34:44.850
It's our responsibility,

34:44.851 --> 34:48.487
and it's our privilege.

34:48.487 --> 34:50.156
Now let me make one thing clear.

34:50.157 --> 34:54.360
My daughter is not weak.

34:54.360 --> 34:57.796
She's saved my life more
times than I can count.

34:57.797 --> 34:59.698
She's strong.

34:59.699 --> 35:02.835
She's possibly the
strongest person I know.

35:02.836 --> 35:05.137
And I believe in her.

35:05.138 --> 35:07.806
I believe that when the time
comes, she will stand with us,

35:07.807 --> 35:10.876
shoulder to shoulder defending Defiance,

35:10.877 --> 35:13.145
but it will be on her terms.

35:13.146 --> 35:14.146
I have to go back.

35:14.147 --> 35:15.514
No, not today.

35:15.515 --> 35:17.716
And in the meantime,

35:17.717 --> 35:20.986
this militia,

35:20.987 --> 35:25.324
this confederacy of the strong
will hold the line with pride.

35:25.325 --> 35:28.594
We will face The Beast,
and we will defeat him.

35:28.595 --> 35:31.497
Do we have an understanding?

35:31.498 --> 35:33.766
- Defiance!
- Defiance!

35:33.767 --> 35:35.868
(all) Defiance!

35:35.869 --> 35:37.069
(Nolan) All right.

35:37.070 --> 35:39.738
That's what I wanted to hear.

35:39.739 --> 35:42.174
Everybody, back to your firing lines.

35:42.175 --> 35:44.109
We got work to do.

35:44.110 --> 35:46.612
[indistinct chatter]

35:50.517 --> 35:53.352
Second thoughts?

35:53.353 --> 35:55.087
Absolutely not.

35:59.092 --> 36:01.193
Come on.

36:07.596 --> 36:08.641
Well, congratulations.

36:08.642 --> 36:12.000
You are officially healthy
enough to execute.

36:12.979 --> 36:16.415
I noticed the vote to
convict me was unanimous.

36:16.416 --> 36:17.816
It wouldn't have changed the outcome,

36:17.817 --> 36:21.420
and I still have to live in
this town after you're gone.

36:21.421 --> 36:24.623
Well, I respect your pragmatism.

36:27.293 --> 36:29.928
I am going to miss you.

36:36.803 --> 36:39.805
[solemn music]

36:39.806 --> 36:47.913
♪ ♪

37:20.113 --> 37:21.913
[exhales]

37:27.620 --> 37:30.066
_

37:30.639 --> 37:33.231
_

37:34.940 --> 37:36.224
_

37:37.418 --> 37:39.933
_

37:40.672 --> 37:43.738
_

37:44.650 --> 37:46.548
_

37:56.516 --> 37:59.451
I apologize to the people of Defiance.

38:01.047 --> 38:02.837
_

38:04.779 --> 38:08.417
_

38:11.056 --> 38:14.551
_

38:14.848 --> 38:17.379
_

38:18.834 --> 38:20.913
_

38:23.176 --> 38:24.809
<i>Difayantso.</i>

38:27.113 --> 38:29.281
<i>Difayantso!</i>

38:33.920 --> 38:35.086
Defiance.

38:35.087 --> 38:38.790
♪ ♪

38:38.791 --> 38:41.893
[grunting]

39:15.828 --> 39:17.260
_

39:17.610 --> 39:20.514
_

39:22.218 --> 39:23.383
_

39:25.070 --> 39:28.149
_

39:33.124 --> 39:35.641
_

39:49.185 --> 39:50.919
[clatter]

39:54.796 --> 39:55.896
Hello?

40:01.536 --> 40:03.270
Who are you people?

40:03.271 --> 40:05.339
What are you doing down here?

40:05.340 --> 40:07.007
Sorry, old fellow.

40:07.008 --> 40:10.611
Wrong place, wrong time.

40:21.474 --> 40:24.257
I'm going into town for supplies.

40:24.577 --> 40:28.013
Perhaps you could go another day?

40:28.014 --> 40:31.049
I promise you Kindzi will behave.

40:31.050 --> 40:32.217
Won't you?

40:32.218 --> 40:34.419
Of course, Father.

40:42.962 --> 40:46.064
[door opens and closes]

40:47.166 --> 40:49.835
I'm not your enemy.

41:06.719 --> 41:09.187
Eat this.

41:10.189 --> 41:13.592
What, a pebble?

41:13.593 --> 41:15.193
Eat it.

41:15.194 --> 41:17.462
I won't. What... what is it?

41:17.463 --> 41:20.632
Eat... it.

41:24.537 --> 41:26.171
You can't force me.

41:26.172 --> 41:29.608
I disagree.

41:29.609 --> 41:32.044
[chokes]

41:32.045 --> 41:33.478
Open.

41:33.479 --> 41:36.581
[whimpering]

41:48.461 --> 41:51.463
[ominous music]

41:51.464 --> 41:59.837
